    "While the implementation of trustworthy automated misinformation detectors remains out of reach, we hope that this dataset at least makes evaluating and diagnosing generalization capacities of misinformation detection models easy enough for wide-spread academic adoption.",
    "One of the central claims in this article is that online content and misinformation tends to change, rapidly and comprehensively.",
    "While 'misinfo-general' represents a large and diverse corpus, useful for pre-training misinformation detectors and evaluating generalization abilities of trained models, it is inevitable that this collection will become misaligned with future forms of misinformation.",
    "For example, with the latest articles coming from the end of 2022, it likely misses the newly emerging category of LLM generated (mis)information.",
